            "failure_message": "Requires a clear admiration signal with positive valence and strong engagement. Caps envy/contempt/disgust so the beat stays respectful rather than sour. Keeps threat moderate so it reads as uplifted regard, not wary appraisal. Triggers only on an admiration spike or a noticeable engagement/valence jump to avoid repeated firing during steady admiration."
        }
    ],
    "actor_description": "Respect hits me like a lift under the ribs—clean and surprising. My attention locks in, not hungry or competitive, just honestly impressed. I feel myself straighten without thinking, like my body wants to meet the moment halfway. There's a quiet warmth to it: a sense of 'yes, that matters.'",
    "description_text": "{actor} stills and leans in with focused regard, their expression softening into open respect. Their posture firms subtly—more upright, more present—like they’ve been pulled into a better version of their attention.",
    "alternate_descriptions": {
        "auditory": "I hear a small, involuntary intake of breath—then a steadier tone, like someone choosing their words more carefully because they mean it.",
        "tactile": "The air shifts with a subtle forward lean; there’s a quiet energy in stillness, like attention has weight and it just moved closer.",
        "limited": "I sense a brief pause—then a clean, focused regard settling in."
    },
